</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">The species was collected in bloom in August and had inflorescences in different stages of development, which suggests that the flowering period may be much broader.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="111" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">The specific epithet refers to the provinces of El Oro and Loja, since this species was discovered at their border.</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/phytokeys.180.62671.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/574521" pageId="0" pageNumber="111" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="111">
